

[h1]Kitchen Consolidation[/h1]

Fixes food fragmentation without breaking balance or immersion.

[list]
[*]Safely combines leftover food
[*]Lets you prepare small meat and fish pieces into usable piles
[*]Works with stews and soups without changing vanilla balance
[*]No free food, no buffs, no recipe overrides
[/list]

[h2]What problem does this mod solve?[/h2]

In Project Zomboid, food management often breaks down ‚Äî not because food is scarce, but because it becomes [b]fragmented[/b].

You end up with plenty of food that‚Äôs technically edible, but practically useless:

[list]
[*]Partially-used cans cluttering your inventory
[*]Many small or partial cuts that can‚Äôt be combined
[*]Leftovers that don‚Äôt justify taking up a stew or soup slot
[*]Cooking systems that punish variety instead of preparation
[/list]

The result is busywork, not survival gameplay.

[b]Kitchen Consolidation fixes that.[/b]

[h3]Important clarification[/h3]

Many foods already support [b]partial use[/b] ‚Äî ground beef, butter, lard, and similar items work fine in vanilla.

Kitchen Consolidation doesn‚Äôt replace that behavior.

It fixes [b]fragmentation under constraint[/b]:
[list]
[*]Too many incompatible leftovers
[*]Too few ingredient slots
[*]Perfectly usable food becoming impractical to cook or add
[/list]

[h2]What this mod does[/h2]

[h3]ü•´ Consolidate opened / partial foods[/h3]
[list]
[*]Combine opened cans and jars of the same food
[*]Items must share the [b]same freshness state[/b]
[*]Empty containers are returned (cans, jars, lids)
[*]Nutrition, freshness, and sickness are preserved conservatively
[/list]

[b]Result:[/b] fewer half-cans cluttering your inventory.

[h3]üêü Prepare fish into Fish Pieces[/h3]
[list]
[*]Fish fillets are [b]explicitly prepared[/b]
[*]Produces [b]Fish Pieces[/b], a fungible pile
[*]Fish Pieces:
[list]
[*]behave like ground meat
[*]can be partially used
[*]integrate cleanly into stews and soups
[/list]
[*]Raw fish remains dangerous until cooked
[/list]

[b]Result:[/b] small fish and partial fillets stay useful.

[h3]ü•© Prepare meat into Meat Pieces[/h3]
[list]
[*]Raw meats can be prepared into [b]Meat Pieces[/b]
[*]Works for:
[list]
[*]vanilla meats
